Static Container manipulation utilities..

equals

public static <E> boolean equals(Container<E> obj1,
                                 Collection<E> obj2)
Deep equality of containers.

Note that two containers that contain the same set of elements but iterate through them in a different order will not be considered equal by this method.

Type Parameters:
E - the type of the container elements
Parameters:
obj1 - the left containers to inspect
obj2 - the right containers to inspect
Returns:
true if the two containers have the same size, and the element returned by their iterators at each iteration step are either Object.equals(java.lang.Object) to each other or both null.

equals

public static <K,V> boolean equals(Map<K,V> obj1,
                                   Map<K,V> obj2)
Deep equality of maps.

Note that two maps that contain the same set of key-value pairs but iterate through them in a different order will not be considered equal by this method.

Type Parameters:
K - the type of the map keys
V - the type of the map values
Parameters:
obj1 - the left map to inspect
obj2 - the right map to inspect
Returns:
true if the two maps have the same size, and the entries returned by their iterators at each iteration step contain keys and values that are respectively either Object.equals(java.lang.Object) to each other or both null.
